<p><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;">Soft power&nbsp;</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;"><strong>Soft Power</strong>- concept was given by Joseph Nye. It’s the ability of a country to persuade others to follow its policies through consensus and cultural influence rather than coercion.</span></span></p>
<ol style="list-style-type:lower-alpha; margin-left:36px">
<li value="1"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;">Kautilya Arthshastra = Saam daan dand behd&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;">5 pillars of soft power = Samman, Samvad, Samriddhi (shared prosperity), Suraksha (regional and global Security), Sanskriti and sabhyta</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;">Kabir = I am not a Hindu nor a Muslim, Allah and Ram are breadth of my body.</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;">Vasudhaiva kutumbakam = global citizenship and all communities a re collectively responsible for their shared future</span></span></li></ol>
<ol style="list-style-type:lower-alpha; margin-left:36px">
