<p><span style="font-size:10.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;"><strong>MEA </strong>has decided to develop Soft Power Matrix to measure the effectiveness of India's soft power outreach.</span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;"><strong>Importance</strong>-</span></span></p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal; margin-left:36px">
<li value="1"><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;">Tool for diplomacy- Act East policy, Connect Central Asia policy, Strategic Aid and Trade partnership in Africa</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;">Create goodwill for India- which becomes useful in multilateral institutions eg, ICJ judge case</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;">Hard power usage carries mass disapproval</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;">Hard power remains relevant for geopolitics but Soft power is increasingly important for trade, investment, tourism, attracting talent from other countries</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;">Soft power also play role of<strong> identity building</strong>. Eg Indian<strong> diaspora</strong> has attachment to India even after several generation outside India as soft power plays a role here.</span></span></li></ol>
